All about tigers: Tigers are the largest in the cat family known as the feline family.
They measure 3.1m for male and 2.8m for female. 
They weigh 310 kgfor male and 170 kg for female.
They are very fast running at a top speed at 65km/h.
They are carnivore that mostly eat sambar deer and wild boar.
Sadly the tigers are endangered so please check the world wildlife fund on how to save tigers. They are trying their best so help too.
